item.description: Unit 10 The Doctor’s Dilemma: ls lt Ever Good to Do Harm? 医生的困境：伤害永远是好事吗？ First paragraph: Medical knowledge changes swiftly, and technological changes make new and expensive investigations and treatments possible that were only theoretical a few years ago. Life has been extended in length, but not in quality, and the debates about end‑of‑life decisions show us how much the notion of a “good life” is bound up with the absence of disease, illness and suffering.
